# [MISER=8] Build 3 Real Interactive 3D Viz Blocks

Build 3 new `m3d-` prefixed EDS blocks. All have real Three.js 3D
interactivity (mouse rotate/zoom). All visualize actual data in 3D space.
All show colorful interactive realistic or real and exceptional looking
demo content if author does not set a data source or set data inline.
All are authorable in UE or DA Live block authoring. All support inline
data definition with guidance, pointing at a path in AEM, or uploading
a CSV file or even PDF report to visualize in 3d.
Blocks live at `blocks/m3d-<name>/`. Do NOT overwrite any existing block.

---

## Blocks

### 1. `m3d-force-graph`
Real data in 3D space. Three.js force-directed graph where nodes and links float
in 3D. Mouse drag rotates the whole graph. Graph rotates slowly by default around
x and z axes so a diagonal obvious slow rotation. Pause this auto rotation on hover
Placeholder renders a sample. Content format: Options are Inline, DAM Path, Upload 
Inline: CSV format `Source,Target,Weight` 
(one per row in block cell).
DAM Path: Browser or enter DAM Path to CSV or txt or PDF file
Upload: Upload a new file which will be created in DAM or as a new sheet
if authoring on DA live, not inlined to the page.
- CDN: `https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/three@0.155.0/build/three.min.js`
- Orbit controls via inline mini-implementation (no CDN dep for controls)
- Nodes: textured 3d shapes, color by degree. Links: `THREE.Line`. Labels.
- Canvas fills block height (default `420px`, override via `height` field).
- **Constraint**: layout runs 15 spring iterations then freezes for perf.

### 2. `m3d-scatter`
Real data in 3D space. Three.js 3D scatter plot with labelled axes.
Content format: CSV rows `label,x,y,z,color` (first row = header, ignored).
- Axes drawn with `THREE.LineSegments`. Tick marks every 20% of range.
- Points: `THREE.Points` with `THREE.BufferGeometry`. Size controlled by field.
- Mouse orbit + zoom. Tooltip on hover shows label+coords via raycasting.
- Canvas height via field (default `420px`).
- Color defaults to random from primary colors if column absent.
- High quality lighting and point-cloud effects, fog, readable text faces camera

### 3. `m3d-bars`
Isometric 3D bar chart. Three.js box geometries arranged in a grid.
Content format: Inline, DAM Path, Upload (hint these may be reusable)
Inline means whole CSV in a cell, DAM Path or upload support CSV txt or PDF
CSV `category,value,color` (multiline in single cell) or
`row,col,value` for a 2D grid heatmap variant selected by variant field.
- Bars extruded upward from a flat grid plane. Top face slightly lighter shade.
- Axes labels on X and Z edges. Value label floats above each bar.
- Variant field: `bars` (default) or `grid` (heatmap grid, color by value).
- Rotate on drag, zoom on scroll.
- Lighting and load-in animation growing the bars from ground on scroll visible.

### 4. `m3d-globe`
Elabore 3d interactive globe with terrain continents and data markers.
Content format: Inline, DAM Path, Upload as usual going to DAM or sheet. 
`label,lat,lon,value` lines (one per row).
Upload supports CSV, txt, PDF
- Sphere with wireframe overlay (`THREE.WireframeGeometry`). Subtle auto-rotation.
- Textures for multicolor terrain snow-capped mountains light green plains
- Exceptional ocean rendering, moving animated even responds a bit turbulently
- Markers: small `THREE.SphereGeometry` pins placed at lat/lon positions.
- Color and size of pin driven by `value` (normalized 0-1 scale).
- Drag to rotate, scroll to zoom. Click marker shows label in DOM tooltip.
- Default color scheme field: `blue` | `green` | `amber` | `purple`.
- Draw great looking accurate continents, subtle pro lighting and textures
- Globe spins slowlly on proper tilted earth-axis with pole visible by default
- Spinning stops on hover/entry then globe can be spun around and data points
- Clicking points opens detail panels on click with nearest city, label and value
- Points use 3d shapes chosen by the author or random sensible ones based on quick
analysis of the data subject or a default set that looks great

### 5. `m3d-orbit`
Decorative 3D orbital / solar-system viz for hierarchy or milestones.
Content format: Inline, DAM Path, Upload as usual (this should be reused)
`label,radius,speed,size,color` lines.
- Central sphere + N orbital rings. Objects travel their ring each frame.
- Rings drawn with `THREE.TorusGeometry`. Satellites are small spheres.
- Auto-rotates slowly. Drag to tilt/spin. Scroll to zoom.
- Labels float above each satellite via projected screen coords.
- Speed is relative (1.0 = default). Set to 0 for a static ring diagram.

