## File layout per block

```
blocks/m3d-<name>/
  m3d-<name>.js      # decorate(block) function, Three.js scene
  m3d-<name>.css     # .m3d-<name> { position:relative; width:100% }
  _m3d-<name>.json   # XWalk model (<=4 fields, definitions+models+filters)
```

---

## AEM model constraints (enforced)
- Max 4 fields per model (`xwalk/max-cells` lint rule). OVERRIDE if needed!
- Or alternately use the controls in the main UE dropdown of component
- Also use subcomponents when it makes sense
- All JSON files must follow `definitions` + `models` + `filters` schema.
- fj.mcp MUST be used for all `_*.json` files.

### Model field summary

| Block              | Fields (<=4)                                 |
|--------------------|----------------------------------------------|
| m3d-force-graph | graphData (text-area), height (text), color (text) |
| m3d-scatter   | csvData (text-area), height (text), pointSize (text) |
| m3d-bars      | csvData (text-area), height (text), variant (text) |
| m3d-globe     | markerData (text-area), color (text), height (text) |
| m3d-orbit     | orbitData (text-area), color (text), height (text) |

---

NOTE: You will have to add options for the swapping toggles meaning
if author chooses Inline, then these are the fields, if they choose
DAM Path, we need to swap to a UE path browser, if they choose
Upload we need to handle the upload. In block editor we can support
inline URLs for assets AND the Asset Selector / crosswalk DAM browser.


